    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="570"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/128</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 424</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-20">January 20,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State refers to the Department’s telegram No. 119 of November
                    30, 1938,<note n="2" xml:id="d570fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1938v02#pg_722">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 722</ref>.</note> regarding the alleged
                    expropriation by the Italian authorities of properties of the Seventh Day
                    Adventist Mission in Ethiopia, and requests the Ambassador to endeavor to
                    ascertain and report what, if any, action has been taken by the Italian
                    authorities as a result of the discussions reported in the Embassy’s telegram
                    No. 356 of December 1, 1938.<note n="3" xml:id="d570fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1938v02#pg_723">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 723</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
